        <abstract> 
<p>Mentions Miss Buckley’s information on roosting in trees [see <hi rend="italic">Variation</hi> 1: 181 n.].</p> 
            <p>Refers to Duke [of Argyll] and his Lamarckian view of change.</p>
            <p>Roosting habits and behaviour of pigeons in Egypt.</p>
            <p>Criticises Herbert Spencer’s works.</p> 
<p>Has finished <hi rend="italic">Elements</hi>; comments on Laurentian stages.</p> 
            <p>Remarks on his health</p> 
<p>and forthcoming work [<hi rend="italic">Variation</hi>].</p> 
        </abstract>
